<subSubSection id="6CBDD680FF1783E7FCF85D54FA05F917" pageId="170" pageNumber="170" type="description">
<paragraph id="2418850BFF1783E7FCF85D54FA3DFA17" blockId="170.[800,1453,1236,1772]" pageId="170" pageNumber="170">
No material of Bunge from 
<collectingCountry id="5CB0C59BFF1783E7FBAF5D54FB7FFAB7" box="[1131,1263,1332,1356]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="170" pageNumber="170">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
was found in the Geneva herbaria, and it is likely that such material is at LE. Of the six sheets collected by Bunge and deposited at P, only the above two probably qualify for isolectotypes, though the printed label indicate April instead of 
<date id="5019A3CBFF1783E7FB605DD4FA98FA30" box="[1188,1288,1459,1484]" pageId="170" pageNumber="170" value="1859-05">May 1859</date>
, and the locality data was written in pencil that almost completely faded away.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2418850BFF1783E7FCF85D94FA05F917" blockId="170.[800,1453,1236,1772]" pageId="170" pageNumber="170">
Although 
<bibRefCitation id="4036F8FAFF1783E7FC695D94FB06F9F0" author="HEDGE, I. C." box="[941,1174,1523,1548]" pageId="170" pageNumber="170" pagination="33 - 342" refId="ref139580" refString="HEDGE, I. C. (1968). Brassiceae, Lepidieae, Drabeae, Arabideae, Sisymbrieae. In: RECHINGER, K. H. (ed.), Fl. Iranica 57: 33 - 342." type="journal article" year="1968">HEDGE (1968: 52–53)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="4036F8FAFF1783E7FB0B5D94FAE8F9F7" author="JAFRI, S. M. H." box="[1231,1400,1524,1548]" pageId="170" pageNumber="170" pagination="55" refId="ref140019" refString="JAFRI, S. M. H. (1973). Brassicaceae. In: NASIR, E. &amp; S. I. ALI (ed.), Fl. W. Pakistan 55." type="book chapter" year="1973">JAFRI (1973: 43)</bibRefCitation>
recognized two species in 
<emphasis id="16D35919FF1783E7FBDC5E74FB14F9D0" box="[1048,1156,1556,1579]" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="170">
<taxonomicName id="E3A7FE88FF1783E7FBDC5E74FB10F9D0" box="[1048,1152,1556,1579]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Fortuynia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="170" pageNumber="170" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Fortuynia</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
the former author correctly observed that there is a continuous variation in fruit morphology from being typically emarginate and as long as wide 
<emphasis id="16D35919FF1783E7FCE55E14FC00F977" box="[801,912,1652,1676]" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="170">
(
<taxonomicName id="E3A7FE88FF1783E7FCED5E14FC19F977" box="[809,905,1652,1676]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Fortuynia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="170" pageNumber="170" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bungei">F. bungei</taxonomicName>
)
</emphasis>
to the acute or slightly emarginate and longer than broad 
<emphasis id="16D35919FF1783E7FCA05EF4FC45F950" box="[868,981,1684,1707]" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="170">
(
<taxonomicName id="E3A7FE88FF1783E7FCA85EF4FC5EF950" box="[876,974,1684,1707]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Fortuynia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="170" pageNumber="170" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="garcini">F. garcini</taxonomicName>
)
</emphasis>
and that such variation can be found within the same population. Therefore, the genus is recognized here as monospecific instead of dispecific (
<bibRefCitation id="4036F8FAFF1783E7FB715EB4FA1AF917" author="AL-SHEHBAZ, I. A." box="[1205,1418,1748,1772]" pageId="170" pageNumber="170" pagination="931 - 954" refId="ref134976" refString="AL-SHEHBAZ, I. A. (2012). A generic and tribal synopsis of the Brassicaceae (Cruciferae). Taxon 61: 931 - 954." type="journal article" year="2012">AL-SHEHBAZ, 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
